## STANDARD Fee Schedule

Normative Standard

Joinder Fee = 20% of Total loss Cost  
Maximum Joinder Fee Cap = USD 300,000,000,000

Payment of the Joinder Fee constitutes joinder.  
The Joinder Fee is final and non-refundable.

Total Loss Cost is determined using externally observable data applicable to the covered surface.

Covered Transaction Volume  
Loss Incidence Rate  
Average Loss Amount


Calculation

Total Loss Cost = Volume × Loss Incidence Rate × Average Loss Amount

Standard Fee = 0.20 × Total Loss Cost  
Fee Payable = min(Standard Fee, USD 300B)

Royalty

A continuing royalty of 15% applies to all active engine execution value.

The royalty rate is fixed at 15% and does not change.

Royalties accrue only during active execution.  
No execution, no royalty.

Engine use is optional and may occur only in accordance with the frozen specification.  
Suspension of use stops royalty accrual and does not revoke joinder.

All artifacts stamped during execution remain valid and verifiable indefinitely.  
Verification is unaffected by execution state.  
Artifacts produced without execution have no verification state.

Joined entities may stamp and verify.  
Non-joined entities may verify only.

No tiers.  
No exceptions.  
No negotiated variance.
